<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,158,365]" pageId="1">
Also the poorly known 
<taxonomicName authority="(Eichler in De Candolle 1873: 145) Hansen (1972: 106)" authorityName="Hansen" authorityPageNumber="106" authorityYear="1972" baseAuthorityName="Eichler in De Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="145" baseAuthorityYear="1873" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balanophoraceae" genus="Balanophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fungosa" subSpecies="indica" variety="minor">
<emphasis box="[446,565,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="1">B. fungosa</emphasis>
J.R. Forster &amp; G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, J. R. &amp; Forster, G." box="[762,962,158,185]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref1086" refString="Forster, J. R. &amp; Forster, G. (1775) Characteres generum plantarum. London, pp. 1 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 4448" type="book chapter" year="1775">Forster (1775: 99)</bibRefCitation>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[1015,1085,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="1">indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arnott, G. W." box="[1098,1276,158,184]" pageId="1" pagination="36 - 39" refId="ref971" refString="Arnott, G. W. (1838) Some account of the genus Langsdorffia. Annals of Natural History 2: 36 - 39. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933809496649" type="journal article" year="1838">Arnott 1838: 37</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, B." pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen (1972: 100)</bibRefCitation>
var. 
<emphasis box="[246,313,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="1">minor</emphasis>
(Eichler in 
<bibRefCitation author="De Candolle, A. L. P. P." box="[451,718,194,221]" pageId="1" pagination="117 - 150" refId="ref1063" refString="De Candolle, A. L. P. P. (1873) Balanophoraceae. Prodromus 17: 117 - 150." type="journal article" year="1873">De Candolle 1873: 145</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, B." box="[735,961,194,221]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen (1972: 106)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from south 
<collectingCountry box="[1103,1163,194,220]" name="India" pageId="1">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1290,194,220]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1352,1452,194,220]" name="Thailand" pageId="1">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, B." box="[144,297,230,256]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nickrent, D. L." box="[309,472,230,256]" pageId="1" refId="ref1393" refString="Nickrent, D. L. (1997 onwards) The parasitic plant connection. Available from: http: // www. parasiticplants. siu. edu." type="url" year="1997">Nickrent 1997</bibRefCitation>
onwards, 
<bibRefCitation author="Su, H. - J. &amp; Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M." box="[591,753,230,256]" pageId="1" pagination="317 - 326" refId="ref1545" refString="Su, H. - J., Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M. (2012) Morphology and phylogenetics of two holoparasitic plants, Balanophora japonica and Balanophora yakushimensis (Balanophoraceae), and their hosts in Taiwan and Japan. Journal of Plant Research 125: 317 - 326. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 011 - 0447 - 5" type="journal article" year="2012">
Su 
<emphasis box="[629,687,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) is described as having elongated, cylindrical tuber segments (
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, B." box="[144,295,266,292]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Su, H. - J. &amp; Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M." box="[306,465,266,292]" pageId="1" pagination="317 - 326" refId="ref1545" refString="Su, H. - J., Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M. (2012) Morphology and phylogenetics of two holoparasitic plants, Balanophora japonica and Balanophora yakushimensis (Balanophoraceae), and their hosts in Taiwan and Japan. Journal of Plant Research 125: 317 - 326. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 011 - 0447 - 5" type="journal article" year="2012">
Su 
<emphasis box="[342,398,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), but photos on the Parasitic Plant Connection website (
<bibRefCitation author="Nickrent, D. L." box="[1087,1250,266,292]" pageId="1" refId="ref1393" refString="Nickrent, D. L. (1997 onwards) The parasitic plant connection. Available from: http: // www. parasiticplants. siu. edu." type="url" year="1997">Nickrent 1997</bibRefCitation>
onwards) suggest that these are subterranean. Furthermore, amongst others, the leaves of this 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1095,302,329]" pageId="1" rank="variety" variety="are">variety are</taxonomicName>
more numerous (15–35 vs. 4 or 5) and spirally arranged (vs. opposite), and the staminate flowers are actinomorphic (vs. bisymmetric).
</paragraph>
